Ok here it is. What if you take these spells and turn them into an AE bolt series with a say 200 range and a 50 foot radius or so that works off of line of sight??<br>
<br>
Envison this: <br>
<br>
You cast at a group of mobs at about 170 range. The mobs are fairly packed together (lets say their are 5 mobs).  Every mob is in line of sight and you target say the middle mob. After casting, Every mob within the AE range of the target mob (including the target) gets a BOLT hurled at them. This bolt does XX amount of damage (perhaps keep it the same as now).  The 3 spell types would have a cold bolt, magic bolt, and fire bolt and there is a graphic for each (I kinda miss bolt spells).<br>
<br>
Unlimited mobs also for within the radius.<br>
<br>
What use would there be for this? Who knows. But I am sure thru trial and error it would be good for something. <br>
<br>
After all we have (post 50):<br>
<br>
3 types of PBAE (very nice)<br>
3 types of Pillar type spells (very nice)<br>
3 types of rain spells (ok spells but resists still need to be fixed)<br>
<br>
So why not use Al Krappar spells as something different? <br>
<br>
Line of sight AE BOLT-TYPE SPELLS unlimited mobs within 50 radius of target, 200 range.<br>
<br>
Just my thoughts.<br>
