<br>
Consider:<br>
<br>
If you want the maximum number of targets for an AE group, you use the point blank AE series.<br>
<br>
If you want to quad kite you use the column series.<br>
<br>
Because your spells only hit as many mobs as the column series, but are much less efficient, if people want to kill 4 mobs fast using ae at range, they will first herd the mobs into a position where columns will work on them.<br>
<br>
If your spells worked on many more targets (say <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  they would have a potential use, but would probably be used in a similar way to columns, but for more than 4 mobs. So I would suggest increasing the number of mobs hit but reducing the radius of the spells, effectively making them column/pillars that work on more mobs but do a bit less damage. Take the same spell energy, and focus it into a smaller area. I can then see them possibly being used then for multi-kiting more than 4 mobs, probably with a wizard partner or two, or dropping in on a large pull before mezzes occur. They would still be highly situational though, but not *completely* useless. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uiudar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iudar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/01 4:13:03 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.ieworks.net/sof/iudarprof.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why...?</span><hr size=1> Al, you must really really enjoy abuse to show your ugly mug around here.<br>
